    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Request<C extends ServiceProvider,R>
extends Serializable
    A Request represents an executable form of user intent. They can be executed in a specific context usually within a ServiceProvider . Executing a Request will result in either a success or failure. Success usually returns the requested object or success message while failure usually delivers an error object or Throwable to the caller.

    A reference to the context is required in order to execute a Request instance. This is basically the same as invoking a function. If you don't have the required context, then you can build an AsyncRequest using a different build on the sub type of the RequestBuilder interface.

    Since:
    4.5
